From: Nikami Worlds Harness <nikami-worlds@example.invalid>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 21:12:00 -0700
Subject: [EXPERIMENT] Treat FO3 NPCs as Fallout actor animation context

Status: experiment, not listed in patches/openmw/series.

Evidence basis:
- FO3 and FNV share the Fallout ESM4 NPC skeleton/KF path, but the current
  animation context gate only enables the Fallout actor animation path for FNV.
- FO3 proof rows continue to fail actor runtime/rig proof.
- run/proof-harness-sweeps/20260707-210852 tested this on top of the 0003 and
  0004 telemetry experiments. FO3/FNV current and auto all still failed. Auto
  mode improved visible body/face coherence in some frames, but actor root/bind,
  rig pose, and detached visual parts still failed.

Purpose:
- Include FO3 NPC records in the same actor animation context as FNV NPCs.
- This patch is intentionally small and must be proven separately for FO3 and FNV.

diff --git a/apps/openmw/mwrender/animation.cpp b/apps/openmw/mwrender/animation.cpp
index 0000000000..0000000000 100644
--- a/apps/openmw/mwrender/animation.cpp
+++ b/apps/openmw/mwrender/animation.cpp
@@ -222,7 +222,7 @@ namespace
             return false;
 
         const MWWorld::LiveCellRef<ESM4::Npc>* ref = ptr.get<ESM4::Npc>();
-        return ref != nullptr && ref->mBase != nullptr && ref->mBase->mIsFONV;
+        return ref != nullptr && ref->mBase != nullptr && (ref->mBase->mIsFO3 || ref->mBase->mIsFONV);
     }
 
     float matrixDifference(const osg::Matrixf& left, const osg::Matrixf& right)
